<br>
I'd just add that you still have to keep your resists 100+ when 55+ or you risk snares and roots landing (with golem rods being nerfed, thats a bigger deal now).<br>
<br>
With any rules set down by the game, there will always be 100 ways players will exploit them.  Zone control for your guild means loot for your guild.  Zone control to me, is what makes the Zek servers so appealing compared to the blue servers.  No lobbying with GMs about who was there first, no calendars, no verbal bashing between guilds, you just fight each other to decide who gets the zone.  IMO, that is how they should decide epic bottlenecks, etc., either by /guildwar or by the champion from each guild fighting or between the two contesting for the epic.  No more whining.  You win, you get the reward.<br>
<br>
